Field  desorption  mass spectrometry  of  anthracycline  to  examine  Field desorption mass spectrometry was applied to a series of underivatized anthracycline, cosmomycins, to obtain  fragment ions which were mass analysed using the linked scan technique without using collision activated dissociation.  The daughter spectra of the various protonated compounds contain sugar sequence information which is in the mass  spectra. The mass spectrometric data make it clear that field desorption tandem mass spectrometry can become a  valuable additional technique for the structural analysis of  anthracyclines.  Kazuo Hirayama,? The exception is  cosmomycin D, which is the largest and most polar of  the  cosmomycins, and  shows  significantly less intense  protonated  molecular ion.

The positive ion FD mass spectrum of the triglycosidic  anthracycline  cosmomycin  B,  which  consists  of  y-  rhodomycinone,  rhodosamine,  2-deoxyfucose  and  rhodinose, is presented in Fig. 3. Cosmomycin B yielded  abundant protonated molecular ion ( m / z  772) and some  weak fragment ions. The carbohydrate  sequence can be  obtained  from  the  positive  ion  FD  mass  spectrum  of  cosmomycin B. The cleavage between the anomeric car-  bon and the glycosidic oxygen may be accompanied by  hydrogen  transfer  to  the  reducing-end  fragment  and  protonation  of the aglycone side (Scheme 1). The ions,  at m / z  658,527 and 370 are weak but useful to determine  the carbohydrate sequence of cosmomycins. These ions  result from thermal degradation in which the glycosidic  bonds  are broken and indicate  losses of  carbohydrates  with molecular weights of 132,148 and 175, correspond-  ing to rhodinose,  2-deoxyfucose  and rhodosamine. A definite distinction is the interglycosidic  oxygen atoms. Those oxygen atoms are retained at agly-  cone side in the FD mass spectrum but are not retained  at aglycone side in the daughter spectrum. Those oxygen  atoms are retained  at aglycone side in the FAB and CI  mass spectrum as well as FAB daughter spectrum.  In conclusion linked  field scanning  FD mass spectra  of the various underivatized anthracycline contain sugar  sequence  information.
